# ⚙️ Concept 3: Domain-Specific Architectures (DSA)

🔥 Very important modern hardware topic.

*(Not Data Structures & Algorithms here.)*

---

## Traditional CPU

Designed for many different tasks.

---

## Domain-Specific Architecture

Designed for one type of workload.

Examples:

* AI accelerators
* Video encoding chips
* Crypto mining chips

---

## Real-World Analogy

Swiss Army Knife vs Specialized Tool

CPU:

```text
Can do many jobs
```

Specialized hardware:

```text
Best at one job
```

---

## Why Powerful?

✔ Faster

✔ Lower power consumption

✔ Higher efficiency

---

## Examples

* TPU for AI
* Graphics processors
* Video accelerators

---

## Interview Question

**Q: Why use domain-specific architectures?**

👉 Because specialized hardware can execute certain workloads much more efficiently than general-purpose CPUs.

---

## Memory Trick

```text
General = Flexible

Specialized = Efficient
```

---

# ⚙️ Concept 4: AI Model Serving Systems

🔥 Extremely relevant for modern software engineers.

---

## Training vs Serving

### Training

Teach model.

Example:

```text
Train chatbot
```

---

### Serving

Use trained model for real users.

Example:

```text
User asks question

Model answers
```

---

## Problem

Thousands of users may send requests simultaneously.

Need:

✔ Fast response

✔ Scalability

✔ Reliability

---

## What Model Serving Systems Do

### Load Models

Keep model ready.

---

### Route Requests

Send requests efficiently.

---

### Scale Automatically

Handle traffic spikes.

---

## Real-World Analogy

Restaurant 🍽️

Training:

```text
Learning recipes
```

Serving:

```text
Serving customers quickly
```

---

## Examples

* TensorFlow Serving
* KServe

---

## Interview Question

**Q: Why is model serving difficult?**

👉 Because models must provide low-latency responses while handling large numbers of requests.

---

## Memory Trick

```text
Training = Learn

Serving = Deliver
```

